verdict.reasoning:
The bug is confirmed by reading both files directly.

In SsoController.php lines 92-99, `fireNoRoleMatch` is called unconditionally whenever `$roles->isEmpty()`, before the `$strategy` check:

```php
$hookResult = $this->manager->fireNoRoleMatch($identity, $provider);
if ($hookResult instanceof RedirectResponse) {
    return $hookResult;   // short-circuits — never reaches the deny block
}

if ($strategy === 'deny') {
    return redirect()->route('martis.login')->withErrors(...);
}
```

In SsoManager.php lines 201-208, `fireNoRoleMatch` performs no strategy check; it simply invokes the registered callback if one exists and returns its result:

```php
public function fireNoRoleMatch(SsoIdentity $identity, string $provider): mixed
{
    if ($this->onNoRoleMatchCallback === null) {
        return null;
    }
    return ($this->onNoRoleMatchCallback)($identity, $provider);
}
```

The docblock on `onNoRoleMatchUsing` (lines 179-189) explicitly documents the intended contract: "Fires when the role mapper returned an empty collection AND the provider's `on_no_role_match` is `'callable'`." The code does not enforce this. No guard exists in `fireNoRoleMatch`, in `onNoRoleMatchUsing`, or at the call site.

Concrete attack path: `on_no_role_match` is set to `'deny'` in config, but a host app has called `MartisSso::onNoRoleMatchUsing(fn($id, $p) => redirect('/martis'))`. When a user with no matching roles authenticates via SSO, `fireNoRoleMatch` fires, returns the RedirectResponse, and the controller returns it at line 98 — skipping the deny block entirely. Auth::login is never reached in the controller itself, but the hook callback can perform its own auth or the resulting redirect can land the user in an authenticated session. Even without a malicious host app, any hook that returns a RedirectResponse to an authenticated area constitutes a bypass.

The fix is to gate the call: only invoke `fireNoRoleMatch` (and honour its return value as a redirect) when `$strategy === 'callable'`; for `'deny'` and `'guest'` strategies, skip the hook entirely.

verdict.fixNote:
